node.text:
@Nature's most spectacular light show 💫 As we've fully settled into September, the much-awaited season of the Aurora Borealis in Lapland is lingering in our minds, as it usually spans from mid-September until March.

The best ways to enjoy Aurora Borealis can be snowshoeing, cross-country skiing, or snowmobiling. Or a from the comfort of your bed, booking a stay in a glass igloo is also an amazing experience to enjoy this @nature phenomenon. 🌌

From 1-8, which is your favorite photo? 💙

📸 @imikegraphics
📍 Lapland, Finland

node.text:
A bibliophile's dream via @madelinestraveling 📚 More than 70,000 books make this library in its hall, Admont Abbey Library in Austria a truly a book lover's paradise!

The Admont Abbey Library is an Austria-based monastic library located in Admont, a small town next to the Enns River in Austria, and is attached to the Admont Abbey. Admont Abbey Library is the largest monastic library in the world, and is noted for its Baroque art, architecture and manuscripts.

Tag your book lover's friends!

📽 @madelinestraveling
📍 Admont Abbey Library, Austria
🎶 Wildest Dreams - Duomo

node.text:
Beautiful glass house surrounded by @nature 🍃
Tag someone you'd spend a night here with 🖤

📽 @sunny_rung
📍 Chiang Mai, Thailand

True love ❤️ “Choose the person in your life who has the power to make you feel like you're floating.” ❤️ – Cintia Zanuni lifts her up her husband who can’t stand on his own so they can appreciate this magical view together. This story is the ray of sunshine we need in our lives, encouraging us to always embark on new adventures and discover the world with the ones we love the most.

Videos and caption by @cinthiazanuni & @hugoecinthia
